To assess the efficacy of our preliminary hits in reducing spontaneous seizures, we developed an automated seizure detection algorithm based on methods previously used to analyze EEG signals40 (see Methods for details) and used it to define a seizure score. Our automated seizure detection algorithm was trained to identify seizure-like events using LFP recordings obtained from scn1lab mutants exposed to light stimuli as a training data set. We then used the algorithm to measure spontaneous seizure frequency in compound-treated scn1lab mutants. Baseline seizure frequency was first determined for each larva during a 30 min pre-exposure LFP recording. Following compound administration, spontaneous seizure frequency was measured again between 130 and 240 min post exposure (see Supplementary Table 3, seizure frequency, 240 min column). For each compound (comp), a standardized seizure score \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
